The storms have spawned tornadoes, ripped trees out of the ground and knocked out power to nearly 50,000 people, according to WTVD.

A man and a woman, were killed Saturday in separate car accidents, and a handful of others were injured as winds gusted up to 86 miles per hour, according to both WTVD and CNN.

Those gusts topped wind speeds during two recent hurricanes, CNN noted.

The male, 33, ran off the road in a torrential downpour. The woman, 50, died from injuries sustained when she was hit by a falling tree limb.

